# Willow Token System

Willow is a themable design system. Tokens are the source of truth for styling and are built into consumable artifacts. This work is tracked in the "Token System" GitHub milestone.

## Prefix
- Every token is namespaced with `willow` to avoid collisions with consumer tokens.
- CSS variables: `--willow-<category>-<name>` (e.g. `--willow-color-primary`).
- Data-attributes: `data-willow-*` (e.g. `data-willow-color-mode="dark"`).
- JS object keys mirror the CSS names via dot notation (e.g. `tokens.color.primary`).

## Build pipeline
- Custom TypeScript build (NOT Style Dictionary). Source: `src/tokens/` -> build: `build/` -> output: `dist/`.
- Two outputs from one source of truth:
  1. CSS files declaring CSS custom properties (primary output).
  2. A typed JS/TS object (with `.d.ts`) for CSS-in-JS consumers, accessible via dot notation.

## Scope model
- Tokens take different values by scope. Scope types: color modes (light/dark), breakpoints, and features.
- The app reacts to scope through `data-willow-*` attributes; breakpoints may use media queries.
- Scopes are nestable in ANY order. The most-nested (deepest) applicable scope takes precedence, resolved deterministically via the CSS cascade.
- CSS emits a `:root` base layer plus scoped overrides (`[data-willow-*]` selectors / media queries).

## Consumption
- Consumable by anyone importing the library (external + internal).
- `package.json` `exports` expose both the CSS file(s) and the JS token object entry points.
- Plain CSS: import the CSS and set `data-willow-*` attributes on elements.
- CSS-in-JS: import the token object and use dot notation.

## Tooling standards
- Tests: Jest (all code must be tested).
- Lint/format: ESLint + Prettier.

## Future considerations
- iOS token export (and later iOS components) is planned; keep the token schema and build model export-agnostic. Currently a research spike only.
